<li><a href="/wiki/Herbert_Giles" title="Herbert Giles">Giles, Herbert Allen</a>. <a href="http://www.gutenberg.org/files/2156/2156-h/2156-h.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.gutenberg.org/files/2156/2156-h/2156-h.htm" rel="nofollow"><i>China and the Manchus</i></a>. Project Gutenberg e-text. Covers the Qing (Manchu) dynasty, published shortly after the fall of the dynasty, around 1912.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Korotayev" title="Korotayev" class="mw-redirect">Korotayev</a> A., Malkov A., Khaltourina D. <i>Introduction to Social Macrodynamics: Secular Cycles and Millennial Trends.</i> Moscow: URSS, 2006. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/5484005590" class="internal">ISBN 5-484-00559-0</a> <a href="http://urss.ru/cgi-bin/db.pl?lang=en&amp;blang=en&amp;page=Book&amp;list=14&amp;id=37484" class="external autonumber" title="http://urss.ru/cgi-bin/db.pl?lang=en&amp;blang=en&amp;page=Book&amp;list=14&amp;id=37484" rel="nofollow">[6]</a> (Chapter 2: Historical Population Dynamics in China).</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Laufer" title="Laufer" class="mw-redirect">Laufer</a>, Berthold. 1912. <i>JADE: A Study in Chinese Archaeology &amp; Religion</i>. Reprint: Dover Publications, New York. 1974.</li>
<li>Terrill, Ross, <i>800,000,000: the real China</i>, Boston, Little, Brown, 1972</li>
<li>Wilkinson, Endymion Porter, <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=ERnrQq0bsPYC&amp;printsec=frontcover" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=ERnrQq0bsPYC&amp;printsec=frontcover" rel="nofollow"><i>Chinese history&#160;: a manual</i></a>, revised and enlarged. - Cambridge, Mass.&#160;: Harvard University, Asia Center (for the Harvard-Yenching Institute), 2000, 1181 p., <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0674002474" class="internal">ISBN 0-674-00247-4</a>; <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0674002490" class="internal">ISBN 0-674-00249-0</a></li>
